<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="446" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d446">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/7–745: Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 446<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet
                                        Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07T00:00:00+03:00">July 7, 1945—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>2472. Sharp protest was made by Brit Ambassador<note n="1" xml:id="d446fn1">
                                        <persName corresp="#p_KSAC1">Sir Archibald Clark
                                            Kerr</persName>.</note> in letter to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> dated July 6 (to <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> 2472 <gloss target="#t_rptd1">rptd</gloss> Athens 31, London 348) regarding recent
                                    criticism in Soviet Press and radio of Greek Govt, Brit policy
                                    in <persName corresp="#p_G4">Greece</persName> and conduct of
                                    Scobie and Brit troops in that country. Statement in Shalitov
                                    article in <hi rend="italic">New Times</hi> June 15 on <persName corresp="#p_G4">Greece</persName> described by <persName corresp="#p_CK2">Clark Kerr</persName> as misleading and
                                    hostile.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>